# Implement Remaining Phase 2 LMS Modules (MOD-02, MOD-03, MOD-04, MOD-05)

This plan details the implementation of all remaining Phase 2 LMS modules. We will construct Mongoose schemas, Express routes, controller layers, frontend React components, and write full test assertions to turn all failing baseline tests into PASS.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The existing `Quiz` model will be modified to support Phase 2 `releaseRule` configuration and per-question `explanation` rationales.
> All new database schemas (e.g., `Assignment`, `Submission`, `Doubt`, `Badge`, `UserBadge`) will align with the Mongoose + Express modular architecture guidelines.
> File uploads (assignments submission and grading) will utilize Multer with buffer checking and validation bounds constraints.

## Open Questions

None at this stage. We have direct specifications for all validation rules, status codes, and user journeys.

